OL,3,CResearch proposes justice system
OL,4,Coverhaul for victims of institutional
OL,5,Cabuse
OL,7,FThe findings state that while
OL,8,Fconventional legal avenues such as
OL,9,Finquiries and redress schemes are
OL,10,Fprevalent, they often "fail to engage
OL,11,Fsurvivors meaningfully or address the
OL,12,Fsystemic nature of the abuses".
OL,14,FThe research proposes a new framework
OL,15,Fof justice to "bridge the
OL,16,Faccountability gap and improve
OL,17,Foutcomes for victims and survivors by
OL,18,Ffocusing on healing, truth-telling,
OL,19,Fand institutional reform".
